This fantastic book is a follow-up to Proulx's How to Build Classic Garden Furniture. Readers will find many more projects, ranging from simple weekend designs to intermediate level projects that require more investment in time and materials. All the projects are fresh, useful and innovative - sure to please both the builder and the user. Readers will also find all the detailed steps needed to build these great outdoor projects without using a shop full of tools. The 15 projects range from flower planters, chairs and garden benches to loveseats, swings and tables, suitable for any backyard deck, patio or garden. This is the perfect book for the weekend woodworker and do-it-yourselfer.


By Danny Proulx
Published by Betterway Books in 2001
